    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a" id="ref1">
      <head>Scope and Content</head>
      <p>The collection consists of two documents (1751-1754) related to the Peacock Bigger estate and attempts to settle it. Both documents are partial and apparent drafts. A majority of the content deals with the dispute between Margaret Bigger and George Craig over the Peacock Bigger estate. Other names includes David Young and Mary Young. The backsides of both documents contain notes on accounts.</p>
    </scopecontent>
